{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775834321929,"sessionID":"ses_2880829efffeiNHKtRVVolQGSq","part":{"id":"prt_d77f953fb001K1pBL9LjK4EgOo","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d77f9461a0016HS9xOFJWMYhqY","sessionID":"ses_2880829efffeiNHKtRVVolQGSq","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":29117,"input":29007,"output":82,"reasoning":28,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.008187542}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775834323218,"sessionID":"ses_2880829efffeiNHKtRVVolQGSq","part":{"id":"prt_d77f9590f001SKv7HvA4bfoBfm","messageID":"msg_d77f9541c001dYFcnKfrdTAqUe","sessionID":"ses_2880829efffeiNHKtRVVolQGSq","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775834324879,"sessionID":"ses_2880829efffeiNHKtRVVolQGSq","part":{"id":"prt_d77f95b4d001GZCvuy4LOv5aK9","messageID":"msg_d77f9541c001dYFcnKfrdTAqUe","sessionID":"ses_2880829efffeiNHKtRVVolQGSq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_22a2607817024e2fad0cfa73","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-012: 会话存储接口定义 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `pkg/store`\n6: - **Language:** Go\n7: - **Size:** S\n8: - **Base specs:** `session-store/spec.md`, `session-store/design.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: Redis StoreSandbox pipeline commands\n13: The Redis implementation SHALL execute `StoreSandbox` as a pipeline of three commands: `SETNX` on the session key with JSON value, `ZADD` on `session:expiry` with score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`, and `ZADD` on `session:last_activity` with score = `time.Now().Unix()`. The system SHALL fail if any command in the pipeline returns an error.\n14: \n15: #### Scenario: Successful store pipeline\n16: - **GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with non-zero `ExpiresAt` and session id `s1`\n17: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called on the Redis store\n18: - **THEN** the pipeline executes `SETNX session:s1 <json>`, `ZADD session:expiry <expires_unix> s1`, `ZADD session:last_activity <now_unix> s1` and returns nil\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Pipeline error propagation\n21: - **GIVEN** the Redis server is unreachable during `StoreSandbox`\n22: - **WHEN** the pipeline executes\n23: - **THEN** the method returns a non-nil error and no partial state is committed\n24: \n25: ### Requirement: Redis UpdateSandbox XX semantics\n26: The Redis implementation SHALL use `SET key value XX` for `UpdateSandbox`. If the key does not exist, the system SHALL return an error indicating the key does not exist.\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: Update existing key\n29: - **GIVEN** session key `session:s1` exists\n30: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n31: - **THEN** the JSON value is overwritten and the method returns nil\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: Update missing key\n34: - **GIVEN** session key `session:s1` does not exist\n35: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n36: - **THEN** the method returns an error containing `key not exists`\n37: \n38: ### Requirement: Redis DeleteSandboxBySessionID pipeline\n39: The Redis implementation SHALL execute `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` as a pipeline of three commands: `DEL` on the session key, `ZREM` on `session:expiry`, and `ZREM` on `session:last_activity`.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Full deletion\n42: - **GIVEN** session `s1` exists with entries in both ZSETs\n43: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\")` succeeds\n44: - **THEN** `GET session:s1` returns nil and both ZSETs no longer contain member `s1`\n45: \n46: ### Requirement: Redis ListExpiredSandboxes query\n47: The Redis implementation SHALL query `session:expiry` using `ZRANGEBYSCORE` with range `-inf` to `before.Unix()` and `LIMIT 0 limit`. When `limit <= 0`, the method SHALL return `nil, nil`.\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: List with limit zero\n50: - **GIVEN** expired sessions exist in the index\n51: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)` is called\n52: - **THEN** the method returns `nil, nil` without querying Redis\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: List with positive limit\n55: - **GIVEN** three sessions have expiry scores ≤ `before.Unix()`\n56: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 2)` is called\n57: - **THEN** at most two `SandboxInfo` pointers are returned\n58: \n59: ### Requirement: Redis ListInactiveSandboxes query\n60: The Redis implementation SHALL query `session:last_activity` using `ZRANGEBYSCORE` with range `-inf` to `before.Unix()` and `LIMIT 0 limit`. When `limit <= 0`, the method SHALL return `nil, nil`.\n61: \n62: #### Scenario: Inactive list with negative limit\n63: - **GIVEN** inactive sessions exist\n64: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, -1)` is called\n65: - **THEN** the method returns `nil, nil`\n66: \n67: ### Requirement: Redis UpdateSessionLastActivity precondition\n68: The Redis implementation SHALL verify the session key exists via `GET` before executing `ZADD` on `session:last_activity`. If the key is absent, the method SHALL return `ErrNotFound`. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`.\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Activity update with zero time\n71: - **GIVEN** session `s1` exists and `at` is `time.Time{}`\n72: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at)` is called\n73: - **THEN** `ZADD session:last_activity <now_unix> s1` is executed\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Activity update for missing session\n76: - **GIVEN** session `s1` does not exist\n77: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", now)` is called\n78: - **THEN** the method returns `ErrNotFound`\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Valkey StoreSandbox multi-command\n81: The Valkey implementation SHALL execute `StoreSandbox` via `DoMulti` with `SETNX`, `ZADD` on `session:expiry`, and `ZADD` on `session:last_activity`.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Valkey store success\n84: - **GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with session id `v1`\n85: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called on the Valkey store\n86: - **THEN** `DoMulti` executes the three commands and returns nil\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Valkey UpdateSandbox response validation\n89: The Valkey implementation SHALL use `SET ... XX` and validate the response string equals `OK`. If the response is not `OK`, the system SHALL return an error indicating the key does not exist.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Valkey update missing key\n92: - **GIVEN** session key `session:v1` does not exist\n93: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n94: - **THEN** the response is not `OK` and an error is returned\n95: \n96: ### Requirement: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID multi-command\n97: The Valkey implementation SHALL execute `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` via `DoMulti` with `DEL`, `ZREM` on `session:expiry`, and `ZREM` on `session:last_activity`.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Valkey full deletion\n100: - **GIVEN** session `v1` exists in both ZSETs\n101: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"v1\")` succeeds\n102: - **THEN** all three commands complete and the session is fully removed\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes via Zrangebyscore\n105: The Valkey implementation SHALL use `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(before.Unix() as string)`, and `Limit(0, limit)`. When `limit <= 0`, the method SHALL return `nil, nil`.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Valkey expired list\n108: - **GIVEN** two sessions have expiry ≤ `before.Unix()`\n109: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 5)` is called\n110: - **THEN** the method returns up to two `SandboxInfo` pointers\n111: \n112: ### Requirement: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity Exists check\n113: The Valkey implementation SHALL check key existence via `Exists` returning int64 ≥ 1 before `ZADD`. If `Exists` returns 0, the method SHALL return `ErrNotFound`. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`.\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Valkey activity bump missing session\n116: - **GIVEN** no key `session:v1`\n117: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"v1\", now)` is called\n118: - **THEN** `Exists` returns 0 and the method returns `ErrNotFound`\n119: \n120: ### Requirement: Valkey MGET orphan tolerance\n121: The Valkey implementation SHALL use `Mget` to load sandboxes by session IDs. Entries returning empty string SHALL be skipped without failing the batch.\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Valkey orphan ZSET member\n124: - **GIVEN** session id `orphan` exists in `session:expiry` ZSET but `session:orphan` key is absent\n125: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` loads the batch\n126: - **THEN** `orphan` is omitted from the returned slice and no error is raised\n127: \n128: ### Requirement: Redis pipeline GET orphan tolerance\n129: The Redis implementation SHALL handle nil results from pipeline `GET` commands when loading sandboxes by session IDs. Entries with nil results SHALL be skipped without failing the batch.\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: Redis orphan ZSET member\n132: - **GIVEN** session id `ghost` is in `session:last_activity` but `session:ghost` does not exist\n133: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes` loads the batch via pipeline GETs\n134: - **THEN** `ghost` is omitted from the result slice\n135: \n136: ### Requirement: Redis password policy\n137: The Redis implementation SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Password required by default\n140: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set, `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty, and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is unset\n141: - **WHEN** the Redis store initializes\n142: - **THEN** initialization fails with an error stating password is required\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Password not required\n145: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty\n146: - **WHEN** the Redis store initializes\n147: - **THEN** initialization proceeds without password error\n148: \n149: ### Requirement: Valkey optional client flags\n150: The Valkey implementation SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true via `strconv.ParseBool`. The system SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: Disable cache enabled\n153: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n154: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n155: - **THEN** `ClientOption.DisableCache` is true\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: Force single client enabled\n158: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n159: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n160: - **THEN** `ClientOption.ForceSingleClient` is true\n161: \n162: ### Requirement: Singleton initialization\n163: The system SHALL use `sync.Once` to ensure `initStore` executes exactly once. `Storage()` SHALL call `initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)` and on error SHALL call `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`.\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Concurrent Storage calls\n166: - **GIVEN** ten goroutines call `Storage()` simultaneously\n167: - **WHEN** all calls complete\n168: - **THEN** `initStore` has executed exactly once and all goroutines receive the same `Store` instance\n169: \n170: ### Requirement: Provider selection default\n171: When `STORE_TYPE` is unset or empty, the system SHALL default to `redis` (case-insensitive comparison).\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Unset STORE_TYPE\n174: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` environment variable is not set\n175: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n176: - **THEN** the Redis implementation is constructed\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: Invalid STORE_TYPE\n179: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=memcached`\n180: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n181: - **THEN** initialization fails with an unsupported store type error\n182: \n183: ### Requirement: Redis Ping response validation\n184: The Redis implementation SHALL issue `PING` and validate the response equals `PONG`.\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: Healthy Redis\n187: - **GIVEN** Redis server is running\n188: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n189: - **THEN** the response is `PONG` and nil error is returned\n190: \n191: ### Requirement: Valkey Ping response validation\n192: The Valkey implementation SHALL issue `B().Ping()` and validate the string response equals `PONG`.\n193: \n194: #### Scenario: Healthy Valkey\n195: - **GIVEN** Valkey server is running\n196: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n197: - **THEN** the response string is `PONG` and nil error is returned\n198: \n199: ### Requirement: StoreSandbox nil/zero validation\n200: The system SHALL return an error when `StoreSandbox` is called with a nil `SandboxInfo` or when `ExpiresAt` is zero time.\n201: \n202: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox\n203: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n204: - **WHEN** the method executes\n205: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating sandbox is nil\n206: \n207: #### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt\n208: - **GIVEN** `SandboxInfo` has `ExpiresAt == time.Time{}`\n209: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n210: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating ExpiresAt is required\n\n(End of file - total 210 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-012: 会话存储接口定义 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `pkg/store`\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** S\n- **Base specs:** `session-store/spec.md`, `session-store/design.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Redis StoreSandbox pipeline commands\nThe Redis implementation SHALL execute `StoreSandbox` as a pipeline of three commands: `SETNX` on the session key with JSON value, `ZADD` on `session:expiry` with score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`, and `ZADD` on `session:last_activity` with score = `time.Now().Unix()`. The system SHALL fail if any command in the pipeline returns an error.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful store pipeline\n- **GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with non-zero `ExpiresAt` and session id `s1`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called on the Redis store\n- **THEN** the pipeline executes `SETNX session:s1 <json>`, `ZADD session:expiry <expires_unix> s1`, `ZADD session:last_activity <now_unix> s1` and returns nil\n\n#### Scenario: Pipeline error propagation","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775834324870,"end":1775834324877}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775834324958,"sessionID":"ses_2880829efffeiNHKtRVVolQGSq","part":{"id":"prt_d77f95fcf0015iTUVGL0Qwh0Nc","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d77f9541c001dYFcnKfrdTAqUe","sessionID":"ses_2880829efffeiNHKtRVVolQGSq","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":29696,"input":29599,"output":72,"reasoning":25,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.008329471}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775834327675,"sessionID":"ses_2880829efffeiNHKtRVVolQGSq","part":{"id":"prt_d77f96a780019pKr9md089IjrS","messageID":"msg_d77f95ff3001EZJfuWwJ5KbTi6","sessionID":"ses_2880829efffeiNHKtRVVolQGSq","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775834387843,"sessionID":"ses_2880829efffeiNHKtRVVolQGSq","part":{"id":"prt_d77f9765a001kx1vzxaQMiI7zw","messageID":"msg_d77f95ff3001EZJfuWwJ5KbTi6","sessionID":"ses_2880829efffeiNHKtRVVolQGSq","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_75f50464d91f45019aa0d44b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-013: Redis 存储实现 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `pkg/store`\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `session-store/spec.md`, `session-store/design.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Redis client initialization\nThe Redis implementation SHALL construct a `redisv9.Client` using `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` environment variables. The system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR` to be non-empty. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful initialization with address and password\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set to `\"localhost:6379\"` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` is set to `\"secret\"`\n- **WHEN** the Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** a `redisv9.Client` is constructed with `Addr: \"localhost:6379\"` and `Password: \"secret\"`\n- **AND** no error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: Missing address fails\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is empty or unset\n- **WHEN** the Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** initialization returns an error indicating `REDIS_ADDR` is required\n\n#### Scenario: Password required by default\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set, `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty, and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is unset\n- **WHEN** the Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** initialization fails with an error stating password is required\n\n#### Scenario: Password bypass when explicitly disabled\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set, `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty, and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set to `\"false\"` (case-insensitive)\n- **WHEN** the Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** a `redisv9.Client` is constructed with empty password\n- **AND** no error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: Password not required when flag is not false\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set, `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty, and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set to `\"true\"`\n- **WHEN** the Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** initialization fails with an error stating password is required\n\n### Requirement: Redis connection options\nThe system SHALL build `redisv9.Options` with `Addr` from `REDIS_ADDR` and `Password` from `REDIS_PASSWORD`.\n\n#### Scenario: Options construction\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR=\"redis-host:6380\"` and `REDIS_PASSWORD=\"pass123\"`\n- **WHEN** `makeRedisOptions()` is called\n- **THEN** the returned options have `Addr: \"redis-host:6380\"` and `Password: \"pass123\"`\n\n### Requirement: Redis StoreSandbox pipeline\nThe Redis implementation SHALL execute `StoreSandbox` as a pipeline of three commands: `SETNX` on the session key with JSON value, `ZADD` on `session:expiry` with score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`, and `ZADD` on `session:last_activity` with score = `time.Now().Unix()`. The system SHALL fail if any command in the pipeline returns an error.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful store pipeline\n- **GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with non-zero `ExpiresAt` and session id `s1`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called on the Redis store\n- **THEN** the pipeline executes `SETNX session:s1 <json>`, `ZADD session:expiry <expires_unix> s1`, `ZADD session:last_activity <now_unix> s1` and returns nil\n\n#### Scenario: Pipeline error propagation\n- **GIVEN** the Redis server is unreachable during `StoreSandbox`\n- **WHEN** the pipeline executes\n- **THEN** the method returns a non-nil error and no partial state is committed\n\n#### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n- **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** an error is returned indicating sandbox is nil\n- **AND** no Redis commands are issued\n\n#### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n- **GIVEN** `SandboxInfo` has `ExpiresAt == time.Time{}`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** an error is returned indicating ExpiresAt is required\n- **AND** no Redis commands are issued\n\n### Requirement: Redis UpdateSandbox XX semantics\nThe Redis implementation SHALL use `SET key value XX` for `UpdateSandbox`. If the key does not exist, the system SHALL return an error indicating the key does not exist.\n\n#### Scenario: Update existing key\n- **GIVEN** session key `session:s1` exists\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the JSON value is overwritten and the method returns nil\n\n#### Scenario: Update missing key\n- **GIVEN** session key `session:s1` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the method returns an error containing `key not exists`\n\n#### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected on update\n- **GIVEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** an error is returned indicating sandbox is nil\n\n### Requirement: Redis DeleteSandboxBySessionID pipeline\nThe Redis implementation SHALL execute `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` as a pipeline of three commands: `DEL` on the session key, `ZREM` on `session:expiry`, and `ZREM` on `session:last_activity`.\n\n#### Scenario: Full deletion\n- **GIVEN** session `s1` exists with entries in both ZSETs\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\")` succeeds\n- **THEN** `GET session:s1` returns nil and both ZSETs no longer contain member `s1`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete non-existent session\n- **GIVEN** session `ghost` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"ghost\")` is called\n- **THEN** the pipeline executes (DEL returns 0, ZREM returns 0) and no error is returned\n\n### Requirement: Redis GetSandboxBySessionID\nThe Redis implementation SHALL retrieve a sandbox document using `GET session:{id}`. If the key does not exist, the system SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n\n#### Scenario: Existing session retrieved\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox document exists at key `session:s1`\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the JSON value is unmarshaled to `*types.SandboxInfo` and returned with nil error\n\n#### Scenario: Missing session returns ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** no key exists at `session:missing`\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"missing\")` is called\n- **THEN** the method returns `ErrNotFound`\n\n### Requirement: Redis ListExpiredSandboxes query\nThe Redis implementation SHALL query `session:expiry` using `ZRANGEBYSCORE` with range `-inf` to `before.Unix()` and `LIMIT 0 limit`. When `limit <= 0`, the method SHALL return `nil, nil`.\n\n#### Scenario: List with limit zero\n- **GIVEN** expired sessions exist in the index\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)` is called\n- **THEN** the method returns `nil, nil` without querying Redis\n\n#### Scenario: List with positive limit\n- **GIVEN** three sessions have expiry scores ≤ `before.Unix()`\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 2)` is called\n- **THEN** at most two `SandboxInfo` pointers are returned\n\n#### Scenario: List with negative limit\n- **GIVEN** expired sessions exist\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, -1)` is called\n- **THEN** the method returns `nil, nil`\n\n### Requirement: Redis ListInactiveSandboxes query\nThe Redis implementation SHALL query `session:last_activity` using `ZRANGEBYSCORE` with range `-inf` to `before.Unix()` and `LIMIT 0 limit`. When `limit <= 0`, the method SHALL return `nil, nil`.\n\n#### Scenario: Inactive list with negative limit\n- **GIVEN** inactive sessions exist\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, -1)` is called\n- **THEN** the method returns `nil, nil`\n\n#### Scenario: Inactive list with positive limit\n- **GIVEN** two sessions have last-activity scores ≤ `before.Unix()`\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, 5)` is called\n- **THEN** up to two `SandboxInfo` pointers are returned\n\n### Requirement: Redis UpdateSessionLastActivity precondition\nThe Redis implementation SHALL verify the session key exists via `GET` before executing `ZADD` on `session:last_activity`. If the key is absent, the method SHALL return `ErrNotFound`. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`.\n\n#### Scenario: Activity update with zero time\n- **GIVEN** session `s1` exists and `at` is `time.Time{}`\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at)` is called\n- **THEN** `ZADD session:last_activity <now_unix> s1` is executed\n\n#### Scenario: Activity update for missing session\n- **GIVEN** session `s1` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", now)` is called\n- **THEN** the method returns `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Empty session ID rejected\n- **GIVEN** empty session ID `\"\"`\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", at)` is called\n- **THEN** an error is returned indicating session ID is empty\n\n### Requirement: Redis pipeline GET orphan tolerance\nThe Redis implementation SHALL handle nil results from pipeline `GET` commands when loading sandboxes by session IDs. Entries with nil results SHALL be skipped without failing the batch.\n\n#### Scenario: Redis orphan ZSET member\n- **GIVEN** session id `ghost` is in `session:last_activity` but `session:ghost` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes` loads the batch via pipeline GETs\n- **THEN** `ghost` is omitted from the result slice\n- **AND** no error is raised\n\n### Requirement: Redis Ping response validation\nThe Redis implementation SHALL issue `PING` and validate the response equals `PONG`.\n\n#### Scenario: Healthy Redis\n- **GIVEN** Redis server is running\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the response is `PONG` and nil error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: Unreachable Redis\n- **GIVEN** Redis server is down\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** an error is returned indicating connection failure\n\n### Requirement: Redis Close operation\nThe Redis implementation SHALL close the client connection via `cli.Close()`.\n\n#### Scenario: Client closed successfully\n- **GIVEN** an active Redis store\n- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n- **THEN** `cli.Close()` is invoked and nil is returned\n\n### Requirement: Redis fixed key patterns\nThe Redis implementation SHALL use the following fixed key patterns: `sessionPrefix = \"session:\"`, `expiryIndexKey = \"session:expiry\"`, `lastActivityIndexKey = \"session:last_activity\"`.\n\n#### Scenario: Session key construction\n- **GIVEN** session id `abc`\n- **WHEN** the store constructs the key\n- **THEN** the key is `session:abc`\n\n### Requirement: Redis ZSET score semantics\nThe system SHALL use Unix seconds as scores in sorted sets. Expiry index score = `float64(ExpiresAt.Unix())`. Last activity score = `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on store, `float64(at.Unix())` on update.\n\n#### Scenario: Expiry score is sandbox ExpiresAt\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt` set to a specific time T\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` adds to `session:expiry`\n- **THEN** the score is `float64(T.Unix())`\n\n#### Scenario: Last activity score is current time on store\n- **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox` is called at time T\n- **WHEN** the sandbox is added to `session:last_activity`\n- **THEN** the score is `float64(T.Unix())`\n\n### Requirement: Provider selection via STORE_TYPE\nWhen `STORE_TYPE` is unset or empty, the system SHALL default to `redis` (case-insensitive comparison). Supported values are `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n\n#### Scenario: Unset STORE_TYPE defaults to redis\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` environment variable is not set\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n- **THEN** the Redis implementation is constructed\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid STORE_TYPE\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=memcached`\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n- **THEN** initialization fails with an unsupported store type error\n\n### Requirement: Singleton initialization\nThe system SHALL use `sync.Once` to ensure `initStore` executes exactly once. `Storage()` SHALL call `initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)` and on error SHALL call `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`.\n\n#### Scenario: Concurrent Storage calls\n- **GIVEN** ten goroutines call `Storage()` simultaneously\n- **WHEN** all calls complete\n- **THEN** `initStore` has executed exactly once and all goroutines receive the same `Store` instance\n\n#### Scenario: Failed initialization is fatal\n- **GIVEN** required environment variables are missing\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` is called\n- **THEN** `klog.Fatalf` is invoked with message `\"init store failed: %v\"`\n- **AND** the process terminates\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775834387813,"end":1775834387841}}}}
